Title: INTERIOR PANELS / TRIM: ROOF HEADLINING: INSTALLATION; 2019 - 2020 MY Prius [12/2018 - 07/2020]

INSTALLATION

PROCEDURE

1. INSTALL ROOF HEADLINING ASSEMBLY

(a) Put the roof headlining assembly back into the vehicle through the back door as shown in the illustration.

NOTICE:

Do not damage the roof headlining assembly or vehicle interior.

Install in this Direction

(b) for Roof Side (w/o Sliding Roof):

(1) Install the roof headlining assembly with the 3 clips.

(c) for Roof Side (w/ Sliding Roof):

*a

Fastener

*b

Guide

*c

Clamp

-

-

(1) Engage the guide and 6 fasteners.

(2) Install the roof headlining assembly with the 3 clips.

(3) Connect the connector.

(4) Engage the clamp.

(d) for Rear Pillar RH Side:

(1) Connect the 2 connectors.

(e) for Front Pillar LH Side:

(1) Remove the protective cover.

(2) Connect the 2 connectors.

(3) Engage the 4 clamps.

(4) Install the protective cover.

(f) for Front Pillar RH Side:

(1) Remove the protective cover.

(2) Connect each connector.

(3) Engage the 3 clamps.

(4) Install the protective cover.

(g) for Windshield Glass Side:

(1) Connect each connector.

2. INSTALL VISOR HOLDER LH

(a) Engage the 2 claws.

(b) Install the visor holder LH as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

3. INSTALL VISOR ASSEMBLY LH

(a) Connect the visor assembly LH to the visor holder.

*1

Visor Holder

(b) Install the visor assembly LH with the 2 screws.

4. INSTALL VISOR BRACKET COVER (for LH Side)

(a) Engage the 4 claws to install the visor bracket cover as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

5. INSTALL VISOR HOLDER RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

6. INSTALL VISOR ASSEMBLY RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

7. INSTALL VISOR BRACKET COVER (for RH Side)

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

8. INSTALL ASSIST GRIP ASSEMBLY

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

(a) Install the 2 clips to the assist grip.

(b) Temporarily install the 2 assist grip covers to the assist grip as shown in the illustration.

(c) Engage the 2 clips to install the assist grip assembly as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(d) Engage the 2 claws to install the assist grip cover LH.

NOTICE:

Make sure that the clip is engaged securely.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

9. INSTALL REAR ASSIST GRIP ASSEMBLY LH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the assist grip assembly.

10. INSTALL REAR ASSIST GRIP ASSEMBLY RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the assist grip assembly.

44. INSTALL FRONT PILLAR GARNISH LH

(a) Remove the protective cover.

(b) Engage the front pillar garnish clip to the front pillar garnish LH.

NOTICE:

If the installation hole for the front pillar garnish clip on the front pillar garnish LH is damaged or deformed, replace the front pillar garnish LH and front pillar garnish clip with new ones.

HINT:

Make sure that the notch of the front pillar garnish clip is touching the protrusion of front pillar garnish LH.

*1

Front Pillar Garnish Clip

*2

Front Pillar Garnish LH

*a

Notch

*b

Protrusion

*c

OK

*d

NG (Incorrect orientation)

*e

NG (Overlapping)

-

-

(c) Push the front pillar garnish LH as shown in the illustration to engage the 2 guides.

Install in this Direction

(d) Engage the clip and front pillar garnish clip to install the front pillar garnish LH as shown in the illustration.

HINT:

Make sure that the curtain shield airbag assembly LH is not pinched.

Install in this Direction
